content:
Other Changes in Marketing Cloud Growth

Marketing Cloud Growth offers other useful features that are automatically available with the Summer â€™24 release.

Setup Experience Was Reorganized

The new setup experience guides you through the required and recommended tasks to begin using Marketing Cloud Growth. Find the updates on the Assistant Home page in Salesforce Setup.

Data Kits and Analytics Packages Were Updated

To support the latest features, we updated data kits and analytics packages to include new data streams and other enhancements. First, reinstall the Marketing Setup Objects data kit and redeploy it in Data Cloud. Then install the Flow Reports analytics package.

Manually Update Consent on Lead and Contact Records

If you receive an unsubscribe request directly, you can now manually adjust the consent status from a lead or contact record. On the Consent Status component, use the action menu for a communication subscription to update the consent status.

Personalize Messages and Experiences with Related Data

Now you have more ways to personalize your marketing efforts. With a data graph, you can set Unified Individual as the primary object, then add other objects and fields as related attributes.

Route Your Incoming Email with Reply Mail Management

Reply mail management helps you route email messages that are sent to your sending domain. Select an email inbox that can receive incoming emails and decide what to do with those messages.

Personalize Your Email with Custom Domain Links

Select a custom domain that is applied to all URLs that you include in your email content.

API Name Field Added to Marketing Workspaces, Form, and Image Content

You can now use API names as a developer-friendly way to identify marketing workspaces, forms, and images. An API name is required for workspaces and is generated for content unless you enter a custom one.

Jump-start Your Campaign Using a Brief

To plan your key message and audience, create a brief. Then associate it with a campaign.

Add Segments to a Campaign

When you create a campaign with Einstein, you can choose how to create an associated segment. Let Einstein generate a segment, select an existing segment, or choose to create it manually.
title: Summer '24 Release Notes for Marketing Cloud Growth
